
Flattening Streams:
the stream interface supports a flatMap method.It is used when we have a stream of collections and we want to flatten it rather than using map()
method and getting the nested stream.
it is mapper function produces multiple value for each input value. it is called One -To- Many mapping




anyMatch : checks if there is an element  in the stream matching the given predicate  // returns True or False / boolean
allMatch : checks if all the elements of the stream match the given predicate
noneMatch : Ensures no elements in the stream match the given predicate
findAny : Returns any element from a Stream





